     =========================================================
 		      Geant4 - Radioprotection example
     =========================================================

                             README
                      ---------------------

0. Introduction.

The Radioprotection example simulates the energy deposit in a phantom.
This application is important in the radioprotection domain.

A monochromatic particle beam impinges on a slab of water and then
on a phantom filled with water.
       |s| /  |  |
-----> |l|/   |  |  
beam   |a|\   |  |
       |b| \  |  |
              phantom

The primary particles (of the impinging beam) can be:
p, alpha, e-, e+,gamma.

The phantom is sliced in 1 cm thick slices.
The output of the simulation is a hbk file containing information about
the energy deposit in the phantom.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
----> 2.SET-UP 
                                                                        |
 -example enviroment with the compiler 3.2                              
 -a standard Geant4 example GNUmakefile is provided                     |

setup with:                                                             |
compiler = gcc-3.2
G4SYSTEM = linux-g++                                                    |

The following environment variables need to be set:                     |

G4LEDATA: points to low energy data base - G4EMLOW2.3                   |

setup for analysis with AIDA 3.0/Anaphe 5.0.5 for user with account     |
on lxplus:
                                                                        |
setenv G4ANALYSIS_USE  1
                                                                        |
source /afs/cern.ch/sw/lhcxx/share/LHCXX/5.0.5/scripts/setupAnaphe.csh
setenv PATH ${PATH}:/afs/cern.ch/sw/lhcxx/share/LHCXX/5.0.5/scripts/    |

 Please take a look to the Anaphe/Lizard web page                       |
        http://anaphe.web.cern.ch/anaphe 
 for more info                                                          |

------------------------------------------------------------------------
----> 3.How to run the example.                                         |

- batch mode:
  $G4WORDIR/bin/Linux-g++/remsim proton.mac                             |
  $G4WORDIR/bin/Linux-g++/Brachy alpha.mac       
                                                                        |
- Interative mode:                                                      
  3) $G4WORDIR/bin/Linux-g++/Brachy
     The vis.mac is loaded automatically                                |

------------------------------------------------------------------------
----> 4. Simulation output                                              |

if ANALYSIS_USE = 1 in the set-up, the output is remsim.hbk             | 
                                 
 It contains histograms:                                                |
         10 (1)   Energy Deposit  (energy Deposit in the phantom)
                  EnergyDep in MeV on y axis, cm on x axis
         20 (2)   SpatialInfo at slab =0                                |
                  Spatial distribution of particles when they impinge
                  on the phantom (x,y in m)
         30 (2)   SpatialInfo at slab=3
                  Spatial distribution of particles when they impinge on 
                  the slab Nb.3 of the phantom (x,y in m)
         40 (2)   SpatialInfo3 at slab=6                               |
                  Spatial distribution of particles when they impinge on 
                  the slab Nb.6 of the phantom (x,y in m)
         50 (1)   e+,e- impinging on the phantom
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of e+ and e- impinging on the 
                  phantom  
         60 (1)   hadrons impinging on the phantom                      |
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of p and alpha impinging on 
                  the phantom  
         70 (1)   photons impinging on the phantom
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of photons impinging on 
                  the phantom  
         80 (1)   e+,e- impinging in the phantom at 2.cm                |
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of photons impinging on 
                  the phantom at 2.cm 
         90 (1)   hadrons impinging in the phantom at 2.cm
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of p and alpha impinging on 
                  the phantom at 2.cm 
        100 (1)   photons impinging in the phantom at 2.cm
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of photons impinging on 
                  the phantom at 2.cm                                   |
        110 (1)   e+,e- outgoing the phantom  
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of electrons outgoing 
                  the phantom  
        120 (1)   hadrons outgoing the phantom     
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of p and alpha outgoing 
                  the phantom                                           |
        130 (1)   photons outgoing the phantom
                  Energy Distribution (MeV)of photons outgoing 
                  the phantom  
        140 (1)   EnergyDistribution of secondary neutrons              |
                  Initial Energy (MeV)of secondary neutrons (in the case
                  the user activates hadronic physics)
        150 (1)   EnergyDistribution of photons 
                  Initial Energy (MeV)of secondary photons
        160 (1)   EnergyDistribution of electrons 
                  Initial Energy (MeV)of secondary electrons            |
        170 (1)   EnergyDistribution of secondary hadrons (pions, kaons)
                  Initial Energy (MeV)of secondary hadrons (in the case
                  the user activates hadronic physics)  
        180 (1)   Energy of primary particles                           |
                                                                        
